},\"scene\":{\"xaxis\":{\"backgroundcolor\":\"#E5ECF6\",\"gridcolor\":\"white\",\"linecolor\":\"white\",\"showbackground\":true,\"ticks\":\"\",\"zerolinecolor\":\"white\",\"gridwidth\":2},\"yaxis\":{\"backgroundcolor\":\"#E5ECF6\",\"gridcolor\":\"white\",\"linecolor\":\"white\",\"showbackground\":true,\"ticks\":\"\",\"zerolinecolor\":\"white\",\"gridwidth\":2},\"zaxis\":{\"backgroundcolor\":\"#E5ECF6\",\"gridcolor\":\"white\",\"linecolor\":\"white\",\"showbackground\":true,\"ticks\":\"\",\"zerolinecolor\":\"white\",\"gridwidth\":2}},\"shapedefaults\":{\"line\":{\"color\":\"#2a3f5f\"}},\"annotationdefaults\":{\"arrowcolor\":\"#2a3f5f\",\"arrowhead\":0,\"arrowwidth\":1},\"geo\":{\"bgcolor\":\"white\",\"landcolor\":\"#E5ECF6\",\"subunitcolor\":\"white\",\"showland\":true,\"showlakes\":true,\"lakecolor\":\"white\"},\"title\":{\"x\":0.05},\"mapbox\":{\"style\":\"light\"},\"margin\":{\"b\":0,\"l\":0,\"r\":0,\"t\":30}}},\"xaxis\":{\"anchor\":\"y\",\"domain\":[0.0,1.0],\"title\":{\"text\":\"\"},\"gridcolor\":\"rgba(0,0,0,0)\"},\"yaxis\":{\"anchor\":\"x\",\"domain\":[0.0,1.0],\"title\":{\"text\":\"Revenue (\\u20ac)\"},\"gridcolor\":\"#252535\"},\"legend\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Category\"},\"tracegroupgap\":0,\"bgcolor\":\"rgba(0,0,0,0)\"},\"title\":{\"text\":\"Revenue by Region and Category\",\"font\":{\"color\":\"#ffffff\"}},\"barmode\":\"group\",\"font\":{\"color\":\"#9898b0\"},\"plot_bgcolor\":\"#14141f\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"#14141f\"},                        {\"responsive\": true}                    ).then(function(){\n                            \nvar gd = document.getElementById('0e33688d-5ac9-4ee1-a508-33dbbae93a5e');\nvar x = new MutationObserver(function (mutations, observer) {{\n        var display = window.getComputedStyle(gd).display;\n        if (!display || display === 'none') {{\n            console.log([gd, 'removed!']);\n            Plotly.purge(gd);\n            observer.disconnect();\n        }}\n}});\n\n// Listen for the removal of the full notebook cells\nvar notebookContainer = gd.closest('#notebook-container');\nif (notebookContainer) {{\n    x.observe(notebookContainer, {childList: true});\n}}\n\n// Listen for the clearing of the current output cell\nvar outputEl = gd.closest('.output');\nif (outputEl) {{\n    x.observe(outputEl, {childList: true});\n}}\n\n                        })                };            </script>        </div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n:::{.callout-note}\n**What this analysis found:**\n\n- Revenue follows a clear seasonal curve peaking in Q4, suggesting promotional spend should be front-loaded into Q3 to capture the ramp-up.\n- Electronics generates disproportionate revenue relative to its transaction count — protecting margin here matters more than volume discounts.\n- Regional revenue is broadly distributed, so a Dublin-only focus would miss a substantial portion of the market.\n:::\n\n---\n\n## Reflection\n\nThis project reinforced something I keep running into — the most useful output of an EDA isn't the visualisations themselves, it's the shortlist of questions they raise. Here, the seasonal pattern immediately suggests a follow-up: does the peak come from higher basket sizes, or just more transactions? That's the next query to write.\n\nThe other thing worth noting is that clean data still takes time. Even with a synthetic dataset designed to be tidy, there were decisions to make about aggregation level, date formatting, and how to handle multi-category breakdowns in a way that didn't obscure the signal.\n\n<br><br>\n<a href=\"index.qmd\" class=\"btn-ghost\">← Back to Projects</a>\n\n",
